This article is a presidential memorandum from July 18, 2014. It discusses the proposed amendment to the 1958 agreement between the United States and the United Kingdom for cooperation on the uses of atomic energy for mutual defense purposes. The memorandum states that the president has reviewed and concurs with the positions taken in a joint letter from the Secretary of Defense and the Secretary of Energy recommending approval of the proposed amendment. It notes that the United Kingdom is making substantial contributions to mutual defense and security through its participation in the agreement. The proposed amendment will further improve mutual defense posture and support NATO interests. The president approves the proposed amendment, determines that it will promote common defense and security without unreasonable risk, approves the outlined program, and authorizes the execution of the amendment by the United States government. The memorandum is signed by President Barack Obama.